## 4. The "Hand Feel" Experience

- Impact Sensation
    - Hardness Words: Firm, dense, solid.
    - Feedback: Very clear and direct. You know exactly where the ball hit the racket.
    - Hold vs. Release: Excellent hold (dwell) on active brushing strokes; quick release on flat hits.
    - Dwell Time: Medium-Long, provided you have the racket speed to engage the topsheet.

- Sound/Click
    - Produces a moderate, solid "thwack" rather than a loud, metallic ESN "click." It sounds powerful rather than purely resonant.

---

## 5. Compatibility & Setup Guide

- Best Blade Matches
    - Outer Carbon: Excellent pairing (e.g., Viscaria, Timo Boll ALC). The carbon adds the necessary kick, while the G-1 tames the bounce and adds spin.
    - Inner Carbon: Fantastic for spin-oriented players (e.g., Innerforce Layer ALC). Provides maximum dwell time and control.
    - All-Wood: Very good on 7-ply woods (e.g., Clipper Wood) for aggressive looping; might feel a bit slow on standard 5-ply woods unless the player has exceptional power.
    - Mismatch Cases: Avoid ultra-stiff, dead carbon blades or very slow defensive blades unless you have perfect technique, as the rubber itself won't help you generate speed.

- Forehand vs. Backhand Recommendation
    - Forehand: Highly recommended. It fits the forehand stroke mechanics perfectly, rewarding full swings with massive spin and arc.
    - Backhand: Recommended for advanced players who have an active backhand loop. For passive backhand blockers, it might feel too firm or demanding.

